1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,720
Get out of my house!

2
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,360
Get out!

3
00:02:44,440 --> 00:02:46,560
Can I come back and live here?

4
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:50,040
I'll give you a lump sum,
enough for you to get back on your feet.

5
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:52,040
But you have to move out of my house.

6
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:54,840
If you plan to stab me
in the back, do it cleanly.

7
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:56,320
Don't let me catch you.

8
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,280
But if we let this continue,

9
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:59,040
Mrs. Mookmanee will gain more power.

10
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:02,280
If you all continue to let Mr. Trai
remain a major shareholder,

11
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:04,680
then I will withdraw all of my shares.

12
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:06,000
You're as money hungry as ever.

13
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:08,120
I care about money.

14
00:03:08,720 --> 00:03:09,960
<i>And you only care about yourself.</i>

15
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:11,680
There's nothing left for us to talk about.

16
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:13,440
I want Trai to trust me,

17
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:14,680
for us.

18
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:17,520
He's a murderer.
But I can't do anything to him.

19
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:19,240
That's really Rut.

20
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:21,200
How did he get out?

21
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:22,840
I'll kill you, Rut!

22
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:24,160
Let go!

23
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:28,320
I'll consider you
as another son of Tritot.

24
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:30,920
And your life will be ruined too.

25
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:33,200
- Hey, look.
- Oh.

26
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,720
Hey! Hey!

27
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,160
- Hey, you little bastards!
- Hey.

28
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,200
- What are you doing?!
- Run!

29
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,240
Hurry, hurry!

30
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:40,240
- They're running away!
- Go.

31
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:41,920
- Hey!
- Stop!

32
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,440
Damn it, you little bastards.

33
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:45,480
Don't run! Damn it.

34
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,240
OUR COMMUNITY DOESN'T WANT
A SCHOOL OF EVIL PEOPLE.

35
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:55,840
Why are you taking them off?
Keep them as evidence for the police.

36
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:58,480
I don't want Mr. Trai to see these.

37
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:05,160
Hey, you're his woman, right?

38
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:07,200
Hey!

39
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:08,960
Take this.

40
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:12,200
- Yeah!
- Go!

41
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,600
You little bastards!

42
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:16,200
Don't run!

43
00:04:16,279 --> 00:04:18,360
Hey, Pakbung, are you okay?

44
00:04:19,079 --> 00:04:20,120
Those pieces of trash.

45
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:21,760
Don't let me catch them.

46
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:23,320
Sit down, slowly.

47
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:26,840
Let me see. Are you hurt anywhere?

48
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:28,800
- It's all dirty.
- Pakbung.

49
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:32,520
Are you okay? Are you hurt anywhere?

50
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:37,280
Too bad. I was so shocked that
I couldn't chase them in time.

51
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:41,480
Otherwise, I would've tied them up
and poured paint down their throats!

52
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:43,760
You're way too brutal.

53
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:45,720
Look at what they did to my friend.

54
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:47,600
You sure you're not hurt?

55
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:49,760
I'm fine.

56
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:52,760
Chill. Easy.

57
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,400
Easy how?

58
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:57,600
You're messed up from head to…

59
00:04:58,760 --> 00:04:59,880
Easy. Easy.

60
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:01,200
Mr. Trai.

61
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:04,520
I checked. They're probably
local teens from around here.

62
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:09,160
It's difficult now.
If this neighborhood doesn't welcome you,

63
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,520
how are you supposed
to open a school here?

64
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:21,560
Mr. Trai, help me wash the paint off.

65
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:29,320
Let's go.

66
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:33,880
Think before you speak.

67
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:36,320
Aw, I didn't know.

68
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:38,000
Then don't say anything.

69
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:42,520
It's harder to get off than I thought.

70
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:45,840
Just like my mistake.

71
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:47,600
Stop right there.

72
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:51,040
I know what you're thinking.

73
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,960
If you blame yourself again,

74
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:55,320
I really will deduct points from you.

75
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:58,440
I hate causing trouble for other people.

76
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:03,680
I tried to fix it, but it feels like
everything just got worse.

77
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:09,880
Come on, Mr. Trai.

78
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:13,200
People only get caught up
in the news for a while.

79
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:15,960
Once something new comes up,

80
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:17,520
this will fade on its own.

81
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,720
I still haven't fixed the real problem.

82
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:23,520
Everything started with me,
so it has to end with me.

83
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:26,680
I need to face the truth.

84
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:30,560
Don't tell me you're going to admit
that you were the one driving that car.

85
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:34,320
Mr. Trai.

86
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:38,160
But you didn't do it.
And you didn't drive drunk either.

87
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:40,880
Then what do you want me to do?
Keep running forever?

88
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:44,080
Say it was all Da's fault
and none of it was mine?

89
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:47,560
Like that?
If I do that, I'd be unbelievably selfish.

90
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:49,520
I don't want to hate myself
more than I already do.

91
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:51,960
And you wouldn't want to be
with someone who's a coward

92
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,640
and keeps running away either, right?

93
00:07:07,320 --> 00:07:09,080
So what did you say to Mr. Trai?

94
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,800
What could I say? I was like,

95
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:19,800
"Okay, I understand."

96
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:22,080
But inside,

97
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:26,000
I was thinking,
"Do you want the whole world to hate you

98
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:27,720
and blame only you or what?"

99
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:31,960
Here, girls.

100
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:33,560
Drink first.

101
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:34,560
‪-Wow.
‪-Here.

102
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:36,200
I made some sweet drinks.

103
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:38,880
Nice and refreshing. Helps with stress.

104
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:41,240
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

105
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:43,000
It's actually nice having you here, Uncle.

106
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:44,400
Right?

107
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:45,560
Yes.

108
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:48,800
There are snacks too.

109
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:51,240
A lot of them.

110
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:52,560
- Eat it.
- Wow.

111
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:57,440
Maybe Trai doesn't want to push
the blame onto anyone else,

112
00:07:57,520 --> 00:08:00,320
but it's not his fault alone either.

113
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:02,080
Honestly, it should be split fifty-fifty.

114
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:04,440
I already told him that,

115
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:06,560
but…

116
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:10,360
But what? Say it.

117
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:13,840
It feels like Mr. Trai is…

118
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,320
Trying to protect Ms. Darin?

119
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:19,280
Or is still in love with Ms. Darin?

120
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:24,440
There you go again, Samlee.
Rubbing salt in every wound

121
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:25,760
and calling it friendship.

122
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:30,800
Sorry, sorry. But am I wrong?

123
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:35,159
Then why don't you try
talking to Ms. Darin directly?

124
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:38,320
Like, talking nicely. Maybe Ms. Darin

125
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:41,080
doesn't want to blame anyone either,

126
00:08:41,159 --> 00:08:43,039
but she's just not brave enough
to face the truth yet.

127
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:44,360
It's like this.

128
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:47,760
Imagine you fart in public.

129
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:50,080
You wouldn't want
to tell anyone it was you.

130
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:51,760
Right?

131
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:54,440
Wow, that analogy really hits the throat.

132
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:56,360
- Yeah.
- Oh.

133
00:08:56,440 --> 00:09:00,520
Hey, if we push
the right spot the right way,

134
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,760
it might finally click into place.

135
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:07,720
Really?

136
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:10,760
Push the right spot the right way…

137
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,120
Da,

138
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:22,240
your friends came to see you.

139
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:25,320
They're not my friends.

140
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:30,040
Why are you here?

141
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:32,640
I know who was driving that night.

142
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,560
And you know it too.

143
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:38,640
Did Trai send you?

144
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,480
No.

145
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:42,520
Mr. Trai doesn't know about this.

146
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:47,880
He's actually been trying to protect you.

147
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:51,600
He wants to give me over to the police.

148
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:54,080
He planned to dump all the blame on me.

149
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:55,360
That's not true.

150
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:57,960
He intends to take responsibility
for everything on your behalf.

151
00:09:58,800 --> 00:09:59,960
Take responsibility for me?

152
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:01,400
Yes.

153
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:03,400
That's why I'm here to beg you.

154
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:07,960
Mr. Trai is under heavy attack,
both online and offline.

155
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:11,920
He might have to sell
his Be Rich's shares.

156
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:14,800
He might lose the company.

157
00:10:14,880 --> 00:10:16,560
But worse than that,

158
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:18,040
he might lose the school.

159
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:21,440
The school is Mr. Trai's dream.

160
00:10:22,040 --> 00:10:23,880
If the bad press continues,

161
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:26,840
he might never be able
to reopen his mother's school.

162
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:32,680
Please.

163
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:34,920
Don't let him take all the blame alone.

164
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:39,560
You loved him once too, didn't you?

165
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:46,800
Please help Mr. Trai.

166
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,040
I'm begging you too.

167
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:54,320
Please help Mr. Trai.

168
00:10:54,920 --> 00:10:57,360
You're the only one who can help him.

169
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:59,600
Please, Ms. Darin. Please.

170
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:01,400
Please.

171
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:03,720
What are you talking about?!

172
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:04,800
Da.

173
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:06,880
I don't want to know.
I don't want to know anything!

174
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:08,000
- Da.
- Get out!

175
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:09,840
- Da. Da!
- Get out of my house right now!

176
00:11:09,920 --> 00:11:11,880
- I said get out!
- Go outside first, dear.

177
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,680
- Da, calm down.
- Get out! Get out.

178
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:15,120
Da, calm down.

179
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:16,720
- Please head back first.
- Get out.

180
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:18,680
- Please.
- Da, calm down.

181
00:11:18,760 --> 00:11:21,440
Da, take it easy.

182
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:26,480
Doesn't look like it worked at all.

183
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,360
At least we can say we tried.

184
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:41,400
Pakbung, why are you here?

185
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:43,560
Why didn't you give a signal first?

186
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,520
There was no time.

187
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:51,600
- I asked for Ms. Darin's address myself.
- Why?

188
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:52,640
Didn't you say Trai didn't know?

189
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:54,920
Da.

190
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,520
Then why is Trai here?

191
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:58,080
- Da.
- Did he come to see the results?

192
00:11:58,160 --> 00:11:59,280
Da,

193
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:01,480
that day, you were crying,

194
00:12:01,560 --> 00:12:03,480
so I called Mr. Trai over.

195
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:06,080
Pakbung, what did you say to Da?

196
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:07,480
I just…

197
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:09,920
She pressured me
to take responsibility for you.

198
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:12,240
She told me not to cause you trouble.

199
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:14,360
That's not true. Pakbung didn't say that.

200
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:15,640
But that's what she meant.

201
00:12:16,280 --> 00:12:17,320
She came to pressure me,

202
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:19,600
to use the love I once had for you

203
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:20,920
to make me feel guilty.

204
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:23,320
That's not true. I was just asking.

205
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:26,840
Pakbung,

206
00:12:26,920 --> 00:12:29,840
I already told you I'd handle this myself.
Why did you interfere?

207
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:31,600
- Mr. Trai, please calm down.
- I know.

208
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:34,400
I know no one agrees with me
taking all the responsibility myself.

209
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:37,640
But you of all people
should understand me.

210
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:39,960
You should support my decision.

211
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:42,480
You should be on my side,
not doing this behind my back.

212
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:44,960
I…

213
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:47,280
I'm very disappointed in you, Pakbung.

214
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,040
Calm down.

215
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:52,880
I'm disappointed too.

216
00:12:53,680 --> 00:12:54,800
I'm really sorry

217
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:56,280
for causing trouble.

218
00:12:57,040 --> 00:12:59,120
I shouldn't have shown up at all.

219
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:12,400
- Pakbung.
- Hey.

220
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:14,720
- Pakbung.
- Da, what's wrong?

221
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:16,560
- Da, Da.
- Da.

222
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:18,240
- Help. Please help.
- Da.

223
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:20,280
Please help. Da.

224
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:22,800
Let's get her inside first.

225
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:26,520
Let's go, Mr. Trai. Slowly.

226
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:30,520
Wait.

227
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,160
Go ahead. Cry it out.

228
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:41,840
Why does it hurt this much?

229
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:44,840
I understand.

230
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:51,960
But don't forget…

231
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:55,840
you left your bike parked
in front of Ms. Darin's house.

232
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,560
Hey, sorry.

233
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:06,520
I'm sorry.

234
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:24,760
Mr. Trai.

235
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:28,360
Well, I'm really sorry.

236
00:14:28,440 --> 00:14:31,120
But right now,
Da isn't ready to talk to anyone.

237
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:35,440
She just took some anti-anxiety meds.
She'll probably fall asleep soon.

238
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:39,040
- Does she take them often?
- Yes.

239
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:42,000
Ever since that news broke.

240
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:46,120
Mr. Trai…

241
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:51,760
I know my daughter is at fault.
I'm truly sorry.

242
00:14:52,920 --> 00:14:54,640
I'll talk to her.

243
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:56,280
Honestly,

244
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:57,920
I don't want her

245
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,480
to keep suffering over this anymore.

246
00:15:00,560 --> 00:15:03,520
I don't want anyone
to be hurt by this anymore either.

247
00:15:35,680 --> 00:15:38,200
Ever since she got back,
she's locked herself in her room.

248
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:40,160
Dead silent. No sound at all, Dad.

249
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:42,640
Kanah, do you think Pakbung
might do something drastic?

250
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:44,520
Pakbung's not that kind of person.

251
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:47,480
But love makes people weak, Son.

252
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:53,320
I'll break it.

253
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:55,600
Break the door.

254
00:15:55,680 --> 00:15:57,280
Let's break it together.

255
00:15:58,400 --> 00:15:59,680
On the count of three.

256
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:01,080
One,

257
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:02,760
two, three.

258
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:05,560
I'm not dead. Don't come in.

259
00:16:09,320 --> 00:16:10,400
Pakbung's safe.

260
00:16:10,480 --> 00:16:12,520
She's safe. Okay.

261
00:16:16,920 --> 00:16:19,680
That was really too much today, Mr. Trai.

262
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:25,640
POINT-COLLECTING CARD

263
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:52,480
PAKBUNG

264
00:16:52,560 --> 00:16:55,400
UNKNOWN: SENT VOICE MESSAGES

265
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,760
<i>Have you seen this news yet?</i>

266
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:12,760
<i>Please stop bothering us.</i>

267
00:17:12,839 --> 00:17:13,520
‪YOU DESERVE TO DIE.

268
00:17:13,599 --> 00:17:15,520
<i>Let us live in peace.</i>

269
00:17:15,599 --> 00:17:19,400
<i>We've already lost one child. How much</i>
<i>suffering do you want to put us through?</i>

270
00:17:57,920 --> 00:18:02,480
<i>I really wish you were here with me,</i>
<i>Pakbung.</i>

271
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:05,800
<i>Thank you everyone for coming today.</i>

272
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:08,720
<i>Let's get straight to it.</i>

273
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:11,360
<i>Regarding the case</i>
<i>everyone is talking about,</i>

274
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:13,560
<i>I have no excuses.</i>

275
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:17,120
Just admit it
and sell your Be Rich shares.

276
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:22,320
Are you admitting
that you were driving while intoxicated?

277
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:25,720
What about hiring the driver
to take responsibility for you?

278
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:27,640
- Yes, that too.
- So what is it, Mr. Trai?

279
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:29,400
Did you hire someone or not?

280
00:18:29,480 --> 00:18:31,880
Uncle Rat was our family driver.

281
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:33,760
That day, I was terrified.

282
00:18:33,840 --> 00:18:37,240
I begged him to tell everyone
that he was the one driving the car.

283
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:41,800
That was Mr. Tritot's order.

284
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:44,480
He really intends
to take all the blame himself.

285
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:48,120
It was because of my cowardice
and selfishness.

286
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:50,880
I won't make excuses. But I beg you.

287
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:54,280
Please attack only me.

288
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:56,600
Don't hurt the people around me.
And please,

289
00:18:58,320 --> 00:19:01,000
don't disturb the family of the deceased.

290
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:06,720
I don't want them
to be hurt again and again

291
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:08,040
because of me.

292
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:12,720
I'm sorry.

293
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:32,480
And what about the lawsuit?
What happens next?

294
00:19:32,560 --> 00:19:34,920
How are you going to compensate
the victim's family?

295
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:35,960
- Yes.
- Right.

296
00:19:36,040 --> 00:19:37,400
What are you going to do?

297
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:39,080
- What do you have to say?
- Please clarify.

298
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:41,080
- So what is it?
- Everyone,

299
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:42,920
Trai has already answered clearly.

300
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,840
We'll end the press conference here.

301
00:19:44,920 --> 00:19:46,800
Wait. And what about
the drunk-driving case?

302
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:49,560
Will you take responsibility for Mr. Rut?

303
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:50,800
His father died because of you.

304
00:19:50,880 --> 00:19:53,160
If you're at fault, what about Be Rich?

305
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:55,480
Its stock has seen a record drop

306
00:19:55,560 --> 00:19:56,760
because of your news.

307
00:19:56,840 --> 00:19:58,040
How will you fix this?

308
00:19:58,120 --> 00:19:59,560
- So what is it?
- What is it?

309
00:19:59,640 --> 00:20:02,120
- Please clarify. How will you fix it?
- What is it?

310
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:03,320
Please answer.

311
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:04,960
Mr. Trai.

312
00:20:05,040 --> 00:20:06,920
Mr. Trai, don't leave yet.
Please answer us.

313
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:08,800
- Mr. Trai.
- The news is going viral now.

314
00:20:08,880 --> 00:20:09,880
- Mr. Trai.
- Mr. Trai.

315
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,320
- Please clarify.
- Please.

316
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:12,960
- We're waiting.
- Mr. Trai.

317
00:20:13,040 --> 00:20:14,480
Please clarify.

318
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:20,040
MR. TRAI, KEEP FIGHTING

319
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:29,960
Please answer, Mr. Trai.

320
00:20:30,040 --> 00:20:31,920
Please clarify, Mr. Trai.

321
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,800
We're waiting.

322
00:20:33,880 --> 00:20:35,840
How will you fix this?

323
00:20:35,920 --> 00:20:38,080
- Please answer.
- Please answer.

324
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:41,800
As for the case,
we'll proceed according to the law.

325
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:43,040
As for Be Rich,

326
00:20:43,960 --> 00:20:45,680
if I caused damage to Be Rich,

327
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:48,920
I'm willing to take responsibility.

328
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,400
I will sell--

329
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:52,480
He doesn't need
to take responsibility for anything.

330
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:53,440
Who's that?

331
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:56,320
His wife?

332
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:57,960
Yeah, I don't know.

333
00:20:58,040 --> 00:20:59,360
Why is she here?

334
00:21:03,040 --> 00:21:05,000
Mr. Trai wasn't the one
who was driving drunk.

335
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:07,800
- Then who was it?
- Who was it?

336
00:21:07,880 --> 00:21:10,520
I was the one driving that car.

337
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:11,920
Huh?

338
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,920
What does that mean?
What happened that night?

339
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:16,280
- What?
- What is this?

340
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:17,960
What is all this?

341
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:19,760
He gave a different statement.

342
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:23,520
Hello.

343
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:27,720
My name is Darin.
I used to date Trai at that time.

344
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:29,640
- Huh?
- Dated?

345
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:31,440
- What is this?
- She was Mr. Tritot's wife.

346
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:32,760
That day, we were partying.

347
00:21:32,840 --> 00:21:35,480
I had only had a few drinks,
so I thought I was still okay.

348
00:21:35,560 --> 00:21:37,640
I offered to drive for him.

349
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:40,000
It was my fault.

350
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:43,680
- What?
- I'm sorry.

351
00:21:43,760 --> 00:21:45,200
What is this?

352
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:47,160
I'm truly sorry.

353
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:50,200
Why?

354
00:21:51,040 --> 00:21:52,160
Is this true?

355
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:54,920
I don't know, ma'am.

356
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:59,120
What a mess.

357
00:21:59,760 --> 00:22:01,480
Was she hired too?

358
00:22:03,960 --> 00:22:05,160
Hired?

359
00:22:19,240 --> 00:22:21,040
Why would you confess, Da?

360
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:26,000
And you? Why were you going
to take the blame for me?

361
00:22:26,080 --> 00:22:28,480
You should hate me, blame me.

362
00:22:28,560 --> 00:22:29,960
Do you want
to lose everything because of me?

363
00:22:30,040 --> 00:22:33,360
I had made my decision.
I had to accept the consequences.

364
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:35,400
Then I'm the same.

365
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:40,000
I've been running from it all this time,
but I never escaped it.

366
00:22:40,080 --> 00:22:42,760
My life kept sinking lower and lower,

367
00:22:42,840 --> 00:22:45,000
and it still felt like
I'd never paid enough.

368
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:46,880
Maybe if I take the legal punishment,

369
00:22:46,960 --> 00:22:49,640
the world might show me more mercy.

370
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,840
Da, listen to me.

371
00:22:52,920 --> 00:22:54,680
We caused this together,

372
00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:58,040
so we'll get through it together. Okay?

373
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:00,400
You mean

374
00:23:01,360 --> 00:23:03,400
you won't leave me, right?

375
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:08,840
Thank you, Trai.

376
00:23:09,840 --> 00:23:12,320
This world is still kind to me.

377
00:23:13,240 --> 00:23:15,840
Please don't let me fight alone again.

378
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:17,680
Don't leave me, Trai.

379
00:23:24,440 --> 00:23:26,600
MR. TRAI, KEEP FIGHTING

380
00:23:56,120 --> 00:23:57,200
You know what?

381
00:23:57,800 --> 00:24:01,200
I should get an award
for worst timing of the year.

382
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:03,480
I always end up seeing…

383
00:24:05,680 --> 00:24:07,600
things like that.

384
00:24:07,680 --> 00:24:10,480
Then I should get an award too.

385
00:24:11,360 --> 00:24:14,680
This is the second time I've been
with you in a situation like this.

386
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:17,160
So, do you think

387
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:20,840
I should be mad at him,
or should I understand him?

388
00:24:21,440 --> 00:24:25,080
Don't ask me. My answer won't be neutral.

389
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:40,320
PAKBUNG, KEEP FIGHTING

390
00:24:56,640 --> 00:24:58,120
I have an appointment
with a lawyer tomorrow…

391
00:24:59,920 --> 00:25:03,920
so we can talk about
what we can do legally.

392
00:25:04,560 --> 00:25:05,840
And you'll go with me, right?

393
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:08,280
I already said "we".

394
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:12,120
We did wrong together,
so we'll take responsibility together.

395
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:14,840
Nothing more than that.

396
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:21,080
But still, thank you, Trai.

397
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:26,440
Thank you, really.

398
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:36,920
Go inside.

399
00:26:00,640 --> 00:26:02,960
- Rut?
- You were forced, weren't you?

400
00:26:04,720 --> 00:26:07,400
Trai made you
take the blame for him, right? Tell me.

401
00:26:07,480 --> 00:26:09,040
Listen to me first.

402
00:26:09,120 --> 00:26:10,840
No one forced me.

403
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:13,120
- I was the one driving. It's true.
- No.

404
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:15,680
They had to have forced you to say that.

405
00:26:15,760 --> 00:26:18,000
They used your mom's illness
to pressure you, right?

406
00:26:18,080 --> 00:26:19,880
Right? Right? Right, Darin?

407
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:21,440
Rut.

408
00:26:24,520 --> 00:26:26,280
- I'm sorry.
- Sorry for what?

409
00:26:26,360 --> 00:26:28,160
You should thank me. I helped you.

410
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:29,720
I did everything for you, Darin.

411
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:32,160
I never meant to hide anything from you.

412
00:26:33,440 --> 00:26:34,960
But I never knew

413
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:38,560
the person Mr. Tritot had
take responsibility for me

414
00:26:39,480 --> 00:26:40,720
was your father.

415
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:44,520
I'm truly sorry. I'm sorry.

416
00:26:54,600 --> 00:26:55,640
I thought

417
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:58,320
you were a victim like me.

418
00:27:00,480 --> 00:27:02,080
I was so sincere with you,

419
00:27:03,360 --> 00:27:05,080
and you lied to me?

420
00:27:08,520 --> 00:27:09,800
You lied to me!

421
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:12,560
You ruined my plan.

422
00:27:12,640 --> 00:27:14,720
How could you betray me?

423
00:27:15,320 --> 00:27:17,960
I… Rut, I can't breathe…

424
00:27:23,120 --> 00:27:25,640
Let go.

425
00:27:27,520 --> 00:27:28,680
Let go.

426
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:38,160
Da. Da.

427
00:27:38,800 --> 00:27:41,920
- Trai. Help me.
- Rut.

428
00:27:42,760 --> 00:27:44,440
Help me, Trai.

429
00:27:45,040 --> 00:27:46,600
Help me.

430
00:27:51,760 --> 00:27:55,200
Until we deal with Rut,
you should stay here for now.

431
00:27:56,120 --> 00:27:57,480
Trai,

432
00:27:57,560 --> 00:27:59,520
will Rut try to kill me again?

433
00:27:59,600 --> 00:28:00,600
I'm scared.

434
00:28:05,120 --> 00:28:07,280
I won't let him hurt anyone.

435
00:28:10,160 --> 00:28:11,480
Mr. Trai!

436
00:28:17,840 --> 00:28:19,360
Four times already.

437
00:28:19,960 --> 00:28:22,600
I'm about to dock all your points
until there's nothing left!

438
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:24,560
- Ugh.
- Pakbung, you're starting to get drunk.

439
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:26,280
What?

440
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:29,440
Who's drunk?

441
00:28:31,840 --> 00:28:33,760
Still? Still?

442
00:28:34,840 --> 00:28:35,640
Still?

443
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:38,640
Still?!

444
00:28:38,720 --> 00:28:39,840
Still not letting go?!

445
00:28:47,280 --> 00:28:48,280
I'm gonna…

446
00:28:49,560 --> 00:28:50,480
- Hey.
- Pakbung.

447
00:29:01,440 --> 00:29:02,760
You let her drink?

448
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:06,160
- She asked for it herself.
- How many bottles?

449
00:29:09,320 --> 00:29:10,720
Three.

450
00:29:11,520 --> 00:29:12,760
Three bottles?!

451
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:17,160
Pakbung, why?

452
00:29:17,760 --> 00:29:20,120
I can't drink
to forget my heartbreak or what?

453
00:29:20,840 --> 00:29:22,800
You really crushed me.

454
00:29:22,880 --> 00:29:24,200
Do you even realize that?

455
00:29:27,360 --> 00:29:29,120
Four times!

456
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:31,000
Four times already, Mr. Trai,

457
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:34,160
that I've seen you hugging Ms. Darin.

458
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:36,080
Why?

459
00:29:37,080 --> 00:29:39,320
You still love her? Still care about her?

460
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:42,080
Just tell me straight.

461
00:29:42,840 --> 00:29:44,560
Be a man.

462
00:29:45,400 --> 00:29:46,320
Who are you choosing?

463
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:48,320
Me

464
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:50,560
or your ex?

465
00:29:52,960 --> 00:29:54,240
Choose.

466
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:56,840
- I'm not choosing.
- Trai.

467
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:58,480
I don't need to choose.

468
00:29:58,560 --> 00:30:00,960
Because no matter what,
you're my only answer.

469
00:30:03,080 --> 00:30:04,320
Yes!

470
00:30:05,440 --> 00:30:07,280
That's it.

471
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:16,120
Clear enough, beautiful?

472
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:20,920
He's mine.

473
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:25,040
If you want him,
you'll have to pay for him.

474
00:30:31,560 --> 00:30:32,960
You're not pretending to be drunk, right?

475
00:30:33,040 --> 00:30:34,840
Drunk on alcohol

476
00:30:34,920 --> 00:30:36,640
or drunk on love?

477
00:30:36,720 --> 00:30:38,160
Oh, you're really drunk.

478
00:30:42,120 --> 00:30:44,160
You chose me.

479
00:30:44,240 --> 00:30:46,800
Then why aren't you hugging me?

480
00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:51,040
Or are you still mad at me?

481
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:54,440
Mad at you? What would I be mad about?

482
00:30:55,240 --> 00:30:57,720
That day.

483
00:30:58,320 --> 00:31:00,200
You said you were disappointed.

484
00:31:00,800 --> 00:31:04,320
You were angry that
I got involved in Ms. Darin's situation.

485
00:31:05,760 --> 00:31:07,880
You protected her.

486
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:21,680
I'm sorry. I didn't mean it that way.

487
00:31:23,480 --> 00:31:27,040
Whatever. I already docked your points.

488
00:31:27,680 --> 00:31:29,280
- Docked my points?
- Yes.

489
00:31:29,960 --> 00:31:31,440
Two points.

490
00:31:31,520 --> 00:31:33,280
Two points? Isn't that a bit harsh?

491
00:31:35,760 --> 00:31:37,520
But you hurt me!

492
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:42,360
I cried while hugging Niuniu.

493
00:31:42,440 --> 00:31:44,320
It was hot,

494
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:46,640
tears everywhere, my heart was breaking.

495
00:31:46,720 --> 00:31:48,800
You said you'd take care of me.

496
00:31:49,400 --> 00:31:52,400
So why did you hurt me?

497
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:55,080
You're cruel, such a cruel man.

498
00:31:55,160 --> 00:31:58,200
I'm sorry, Pakbung. I'm really sorry.

499
00:31:58,800 --> 00:32:01,960
I know you did it for me,
and I still blamed you.

500
00:32:03,080 --> 00:32:04,320
I'm sorry.

501
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:06,480
I'm terrible, aren't I?

502
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:09,640
Yes, really terrible.

503
00:32:10,800 --> 00:32:14,120
Even knowing how bad I am,
you still care about me.

504
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:16,800
Thank you so much.

505
00:32:18,480 --> 00:32:19,560
You know,

506
00:32:20,800 --> 00:32:23,400
when I saw you at the press conference…

507
00:32:27,880 --> 00:32:29,600
I was very happy.

508
00:32:31,560 --> 00:32:35,000
You were like a star, like light.

509
00:32:35,080 --> 00:32:37,400
You made me brave instantly.

510
00:32:38,760 --> 00:32:41,760
I know. That's why I went.

511
00:32:46,160 --> 00:32:47,400
Then forgive me, okay?

512
00:32:52,080 --> 00:32:55,440
I wasn't very nice either.

513
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:02,800
I'm sorry

514
00:33:03,800 --> 00:33:05,960
for doing things
without talking to you first.

515
00:33:08,720 --> 00:33:10,920
You can dock my points too,

516
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:12,720
if you want.

517
00:33:13,520 --> 00:33:16,480
Oh, who would ever dock your points?

518
00:33:17,320 --> 00:33:18,400
Keep them.

519
00:33:19,240 --> 00:33:22,000
Docking each other back and forth,
there'd be nothing left anyway.

520
00:33:24,960 --> 00:33:26,360
So I'll punish you instead.

521
00:33:29,760 --> 00:33:31,480
You're trying to sell me out like that,

522
00:33:33,040 --> 00:33:34,200
so you deserve a punishment.

523
00:33:40,360 --> 00:33:41,560
Hey, Mr. Trai!

524
00:33:46,400 --> 00:33:48,360
Aw,

525
00:33:48,440 --> 00:33:50,320
what are you doing to me?

526
00:33:50,400 --> 00:33:53,760
Take me on a triple-loop roller coaster?

527
00:33:53,840 --> 00:33:55,160
Make me flip?

528
00:33:55,240 --> 00:33:57,120
You're crazy.

529
00:33:58,280 --> 00:34:00,120
I can't wait anymore.

530
00:34:00,720 --> 00:34:01,600
Let's go!

531
00:34:04,080 --> 00:34:06,800
Go.

532
00:34:08,440 --> 00:34:09,679
Fine.

533
00:34:10,719 --> 00:34:12,360
You're definitely not sleeping tonight.

534
00:34:13,440 --> 00:34:14,520
What was that just now?

535
00:34:25,280 --> 00:34:26,560
Let's go.

536
00:34:48,239 --> 00:34:50,120
Drinking it all won't help anything.

537
00:34:50,840 --> 00:34:52,800
Trai already took Pakbung upstairs.

538
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:55,159
So?

539
00:35:00,240 --> 00:35:02,160
The real loser

540
00:35:02,240 --> 00:35:05,560
is someone who has a chance to fight
but refuses to fight.

541
00:35:07,360 --> 00:35:08,840
Who's gonna be like you?

542
00:35:08,920 --> 00:35:12,400
Playing the saint, sacrificing yourself,
confessing after running away for years.

543
00:35:14,680 --> 00:35:16,720
You think that'll soften Trai's heart?

544
00:35:18,200 --> 00:35:20,600
He's not stupid.
He won't make the same mistake twice.

545
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:25,080
Then we'll see

546
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:28,840
if I can make Trai
willingly fall for me again.

547
00:36:10,920 --> 00:36:12,240
This is Mr. Trai's room.

548
00:36:14,080 --> 00:36:15,520
How did I end up here?

549
00:36:31,960 --> 00:36:34,160
If you're trying to provoke Darin,

550
00:36:38,840 --> 00:36:40,960
don't do it by seducing me.

551
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:07,920
Next time, it won't stop at just a kiss.

552
00:37:13,160 --> 00:37:14,240
Go take a shower.

553
00:37:27,920 --> 00:37:28,920
Pakbung.

554
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:30,560
What the hell did you do?

555
00:37:32,560 --> 00:37:36,120
I was trying to tease Ms. Darin
and almost got myself in trouble.

556
00:38:00,240 --> 00:38:03,160
<i>If you have a headache,</i>
<i>I left some hangover medicine for you.</i>

557
00:38:03,240 --> 00:38:05,960
<i>I asked Lee to bring your clothes.</i>

558
00:38:06,040 --> 00:38:07,880
<i>I have an appointment with the lawyer,</i>
<i>so I had to leave early.</i>

559
00:38:07,960 --> 00:38:10,720
<i>I'll call you after I'm done, my love.</i>

560
00:38:11,320 --> 00:38:14,560
<i>Your handsome boyfriend. Kisses.</i>

561
00:38:21,960 --> 00:38:23,480
Damn it.

562
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:27,280
It's because you're this sweet
that I completely lose my composure.

563
00:38:35,600 --> 00:38:37,680
Have I turned into someone this lovesick?

564
00:38:44,880 --> 00:38:45,880
SAMLEE

565
00:38:53,880 --> 00:38:56,000
- Hello?
- <i>Pakbung, where are you?</i>

566
00:38:56,080 --> 00:38:58,760
<i>You're not dead, right?</i>
<i>Why didn't you come to work?</i>

567
00:39:00,120 --> 00:39:01,240
Work?!

568
00:39:01,960 --> 00:39:02,840
Hey?

569
00:39:04,040 --> 00:39:08,040
As of now, no one has filed a request
with the court to reopen the case,

570
00:39:08,640 --> 00:39:09,840
neither the public prosecutor

571
00:39:09,920 --> 00:39:12,200
nor the family of the stand-in.

572
00:39:13,240 --> 00:39:14,360
So…

573
00:39:15,160 --> 00:39:16,800
if no one reopens the case,

574
00:39:17,520 --> 00:39:19,120
that means I won't go to prison?

575
00:39:22,840 --> 00:39:23,960
What about the matter I asked about?

576
00:39:24,720 --> 00:39:25,800
There's good news.

577
00:39:36,240 --> 00:39:37,520
Please.

578
00:39:48,960 --> 00:39:52,880
So you disappeared and didn't answer me
because you slept over at his place?

579
00:39:54,320 --> 00:39:56,840
You can scold me. Just don't go too hard.

580
00:39:58,040 --> 00:39:59,320
Why would I scold you?

581
00:39:59,400 --> 00:40:02,360
You didn't come to work,
so I got your shift instead. That's great.

582
00:40:11,640 --> 00:40:12,840
I don't like it.

583
00:40:13,440 --> 00:40:17,120
You don't like Mr. Trai? Why?
Was his technique not good enough?

584
00:40:22,480 --> 00:40:24,840
Or you don't like that I took your shift?

585
00:40:25,560 --> 00:40:27,240
Fine, take your job back.

586
00:40:27,320 --> 00:40:29,680
I was just helping
so Petch wouldn't get yelled at.

587
00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:31,800
- Take it back.
- Ugh. No.

588
00:40:31,880 --> 00:40:33,880
I don't like myself.

589
00:40:34,440 --> 00:40:36,360
I don't like how I forgot everything,

590
00:40:36,440 --> 00:40:39,040
forgot work, forgot making money, forgot…

591
00:40:40,880 --> 00:40:42,800
I forgot I have English class today!

592
00:40:43,400 --> 00:40:44,760
Ugh.

593
00:40:49,920 --> 00:40:51,800
- Please cover for me.
- Okay.

594
00:40:57,080 --> 00:40:58,480
Thank you for coming.

595
00:40:59,440 --> 00:41:02,760
We didn't want to.
We just wanted to see her clearly.

596
00:41:13,120 --> 00:41:14,800
I'm the one…

597
00:41:16,320 --> 00:41:18,920
who drove the car that hit your son.

598
00:41:23,400 --> 00:41:25,320
I'm so sorry.

599
00:41:25,400 --> 00:41:27,120
I'm truly sorry.

600
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:31,320
Was it painful…

601
00:41:33,200 --> 00:41:35,720
carrying all of this alone?

602
00:41:36,440 --> 00:41:40,480
If you'd told the truth since that day,
it might not have turned out this badly.

603
00:41:45,920 --> 00:41:49,760
You're the one who sent apology letters
to us every month, aren't you?

604
00:41:51,320 --> 00:41:53,040
I wanted to apologize in person.

605
00:41:53,760 --> 00:41:56,400
But I knew you probably
wouldn't want to see me.

606
00:41:57,320 --> 00:41:59,400
If it made you uncomfortable,

607
00:42:00,280 --> 00:42:01,280
I'm sorry.

608
00:42:02,080 --> 00:42:04,640
At least you tried.

609
00:42:05,760 --> 00:42:07,040
We won't pursue the case.

610
00:42:07,840 --> 00:42:09,240
We won't reopen it,

611
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:11,400
won't sue.

612
00:42:12,440 --> 00:42:13,600
We're old.

613
00:42:14,200 --> 00:42:17,120
Going to court all the time is too much.

614
00:42:17,200 --> 00:42:19,960
And you don't need
to send apology letters anymore.

615
00:42:20,040 --> 00:42:23,440
The monthly compensation,
you can stop that too.

616
00:42:23,520 --> 00:42:26,800
Stop sending people
to take care of us too.

617
00:42:27,440 --> 00:42:30,800
Let it end right here, right now.

618
00:42:35,240 --> 00:42:37,200
We forgive you.

619
00:42:38,240 --> 00:42:41,160
From now on, live your lives well.

620
00:42:46,280 --> 00:42:47,840
Thank you.

621
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:50,920
‪Thank you.

622
00:43:12,040 --> 00:43:12,920
Mr. Trai,

623
00:43:13,880 --> 00:43:15,040
you feel relieved now, don't you?

624
00:43:15,120 --> 00:43:16,920
That the doctor's family forgave you.

625
00:43:18,120 --> 00:43:19,000
It feels lighter.

626
00:43:21,360 --> 00:43:23,920
What did he mean earlier about the money?

627
00:43:24,520 --> 00:43:28,040
Oh, Mr. Tritot ordered us

628
00:43:28,120 --> 00:43:31,360
to transfer money to the doctor's family
every month since the incident.

629
00:43:31,440 --> 00:43:32,720
No exceptions.

630
00:43:32,800 --> 00:43:34,960
He also told me to regularly check

631
00:43:35,040 --> 00:43:37,880
if they needed anything,
so that we could help them.

632
00:43:37,960 --> 00:43:39,240
My dad?

633
00:43:39,320 --> 00:43:42,600
Mr. Tritot has been taking care
of them quietly all this time.

634
00:43:45,600 --> 00:43:47,720
Then why didn't you guys tell me?

635
00:43:48,320 --> 00:43:49,280
You never asked.

636
00:43:54,880 --> 00:43:57,440
Should we go make merit for your dad?

637
00:43:58,440 --> 00:44:00,560
You must miss him.

638
00:44:00,640 --> 00:44:03,680
I'd like to apologize to him too.

639
00:44:03,760 --> 00:44:06,280
I'd like to clear up
everything from the past,

640
00:44:06,360 --> 00:44:07,640
so I can truly start over.

641
00:44:10,400 --> 00:44:11,400
Sure.

642
00:44:12,520 --> 00:44:14,280
Are you going now? Prarop will take you.

643
00:44:15,880 --> 00:44:17,720
- And you?
- I'm going to see Pakbung.

644
00:44:19,400 --> 00:44:21,280
Lee, you're coming with me.
Prarop, take Da.

645
00:44:21,360 --> 00:44:22,400
Yes, sir.

646
00:44:36,480 --> 00:44:38,120
Da. Da.

647
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:40,080
- Da, are you okay?
- Ms. Da.

648
00:44:40,680 --> 00:44:41,520
Are you okay?

649
00:44:53,320 --> 00:44:56,560
What's wrong? Why do you look so down?
You couldn't focus in class?

650
00:45:01,760 --> 00:45:03,600
There are ten classes in the course.

651
00:45:03,680 --> 00:45:06,120
I've already missed two,
and I was late for another one.

652
00:45:06,880 --> 00:45:07,840
Great job, Pakbung!

653
00:45:10,200 --> 00:45:11,200
Hey!

654
00:45:14,160 --> 00:45:15,520
Just take the whole thing then.

655
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:17,720
I'm full.

656
00:45:20,160 --> 00:45:24,120
Here, here, your pay for today. 800. Oops.

657
00:45:25,000 --> 00:45:25,840
800?

658
00:45:25,920 --> 00:45:27,200
- Yeah.
- Wow.

659
00:45:27,280 --> 00:45:29,040
That's a lot.

660
00:45:29,120 --> 00:45:30,400
Petch added extra

661
00:45:30,480 --> 00:45:32,680
because he called you in so suddenly.

662
00:45:35,080 --> 00:45:36,880
I want money too.

663
00:45:38,160 --> 00:45:39,800
Then go ask Mr. Trai.

664
00:45:39,880 --> 00:45:40,880
Yeah.

665
00:45:43,800 --> 00:45:44,840
No way.

666
00:45:45,440 --> 00:45:48,320
I want to work.
I want to be a millionaire.

667
00:45:48,400 --> 00:45:50,360
I don't want to go crazy over a man.

668
00:45:52,080 --> 00:45:53,000
‪Great.

669
00:45:58,600 --> 00:46:00,040
MR. TRAI

670
00:46:04,680 --> 00:46:06,200
Yes, Mr. Trai?

671
00:46:07,240 --> 00:46:09,000
Are you done talking to the lawyer?

672
00:46:10,560 --> 00:46:11,800
Look at that different tone.

673
00:46:11,880 --> 00:46:14,000
And she said
she didn't want to go crazy over a man.

674
00:46:18,280 --> 00:46:19,160
<i>I'm done,</i>

675
00:46:19,240 --> 00:46:20,280
but can you wait a moment?

676
00:46:20,360 --> 00:46:21,840
There was a bit of an accident.

677
00:46:22,840 --> 00:46:24,560
What? An accident?

678
00:46:26,840 --> 00:46:30,920
Where are you? Are you badly hurt?
I'll come to you right now.

679
00:46:31,000 --> 00:46:32,360
I'm fine,

680
00:46:33,480 --> 00:46:34,480
but Da got sideswiped by a car.

681
00:46:35,640 --> 00:46:36,640
Ms. Darin?

682
00:46:36,720 --> 00:46:38,480
I think it was Rut.

683
00:46:40,080 --> 00:46:41,360
Prarop is looking for evidence now.

684
00:46:41,960 --> 00:46:44,480
Is Ms. Darin badly hurt?

685
00:46:45,600 --> 00:46:48,280
From what I can see, not too bad.
We're waiting for the X-ray results.

686
00:46:49,280 --> 00:46:50,960
I'm at the hospital.
Do you want to come here?

687
00:46:51,040 --> 00:46:53,040
I can have Lee pick you up
if you want to be here with me.

688
00:46:56,640 --> 00:46:58,680
Is life outside too comfortable for you?

689
00:46:59,480 --> 00:47:00,920
You want to get yourself
thrown back into jail?

690
00:47:02,720 --> 00:47:04,040
I'm confident

691
00:47:04,120 --> 00:47:06,960
Trai won't find any evidence
that leads back to me.

692
00:47:07,040 --> 00:47:08,400
Of course he won't.

693
00:47:08,920 --> 00:47:12,320
Because I'm the one who ordered my people
to take care of the evidence for you.

694
00:47:13,640 --> 00:47:15,200
I did it because I had a plan.

695
00:47:16,120 --> 00:47:17,240
Mom,

696
00:47:17,320 --> 00:47:18,760
just admit it.

697
00:47:18,840 --> 00:47:21,800
This time,
you chose the worst helper possible.

698
00:47:22,560 --> 00:47:25,840
Hey, if you're too stupid
to do anything smart,

699
00:47:25,920 --> 00:47:27,440
then just go back to jail.

700
00:47:28,280 --> 00:47:32,080
Or if you're only good at killing people,
at least do it properly for once.

701
00:47:32,160 --> 00:47:34,760
Darin will make Trai and Pakbung turn
against each other.

702
00:47:34,840 --> 00:47:35,840
When that happens,

703
00:47:35,920 --> 00:47:37,840
Trai will be weak enough

704
00:47:37,920 --> 00:47:40,640
for us to deal with easily.

705
00:47:41,960 --> 00:47:44,920
I'll be waiting to see your results, Rut.

706
00:47:45,000 --> 00:47:45,960
Yes.

707
00:48:07,640 --> 00:48:08,680
Does it hurt?

708
00:48:12,240 --> 00:48:14,720
It's just a sharp pain

709
00:48:15,480 --> 00:48:16,520
where I got hit.

710
00:48:20,640 --> 00:48:22,400
Here's the medicine.

711
00:48:26,800 --> 00:48:28,360
It was Rut again, right?

712
00:48:30,520 --> 00:48:32,680
He really is going to kill me.

713
00:48:33,840 --> 00:48:35,800
Then stay inside for now.
Don't go anywhere.

714
00:48:35,880 --> 00:48:37,520
I'll deal with him as soon as possible.

715
00:48:38,120 --> 00:48:40,640
But he's been in and out
of this house before,

716
00:48:40,720 --> 00:48:43,120
and he even hurt Mr. Tritot too.

717
00:48:43,800 --> 00:48:46,320
What if he sneaks in tonight?

718
00:48:51,160 --> 00:48:52,560
How are you supposed
to sleep alone tonight?

719
00:48:59,080 --> 00:49:00,400
Lee. Prarop.

720
00:49:02,800 --> 00:49:03,840
Yes, sir.

721
00:49:07,840 --> 00:49:10,960
Tonight, we'll stay with you,
Ms. Darin, for your safety.

722
00:49:12,400 --> 00:49:13,680
If anything happens,
scream as loud as you can.

723
00:49:13,760 --> 00:49:16,160
These two are quick.
They'll help you right away.

724
00:49:16,240 --> 00:49:17,160
I'm counting on you.

725
00:49:21,560 --> 00:49:23,880
Ms. Darin, you can't walk, right?
I can carry you.

726
00:49:24,520 --> 00:49:25,400
No, no need.

727
00:49:26,280 --> 00:49:27,640
You can get on my back too.

728
00:49:27,720 --> 00:49:29,520
- Oh?
- Can you walk, Ms. Darin?

729
00:49:29,600 --> 00:49:31,080
If you can, help me carry this.

730
00:49:31,160 --> 00:49:32,920
- It's really heavy. Hey.
- Ms. Darin.

731
00:49:33,000 --> 00:49:34,800
- Ms. Darin!
- Ms. Darin.

732
00:49:41,400 --> 00:49:43,360
You'll never keep up
with someone like Darin.

733
00:49:51,520 --> 00:49:53,000
You said the same thing Dad did.

734
00:49:53,080 --> 00:49:54,320
Why?

735
00:49:54,400 --> 00:49:56,720
Is Da some kind
of wind spirit or a runner?

736
00:49:58,960 --> 00:50:00,480
Do you seriously not see

737
00:50:00,560 --> 00:50:03,160
she's trying to force her way
back into your life,

738
00:50:03,240 --> 00:50:04,600
using Rut as an excuse?

739
00:50:05,920 --> 00:50:07,200
I don't know.

740
00:50:09,440 --> 00:50:11,360
Psych. Come on.

741
00:50:12,200 --> 00:50:15,000
That's why I'm thinking
about how to deal with Rut right now.

742
00:50:15,080 --> 00:50:16,760
So that means

743
00:50:16,840 --> 00:50:20,800
until you catch Rut, you'll just let Darin
keep circling around your life like this?

744
00:50:22,000 --> 00:50:23,320
Hey, Trai.

745
00:50:23,400 --> 00:50:25,720
How long do you expect
Pakbung to endure this?

746
00:50:26,920 --> 00:50:28,880
I've cleared things up with her.
We understand each other.

747
00:50:30,280 --> 00:50:32,040
And I will catch Rut.

748
00:50:35,880 --> 00:50:37,240
So help me out too.

749
00:50:37,840 --> 00:50:39,720
Alright, Mr. Chairman?

750
00:50:48,680 --> 00:50:49,720
Fine.

751
00:50:51,160 --> 00:50:52,720
I'll help you, Trai.

752
00:51:09,200 --> 00:51:10,960
Today, I have to make money

753
00:51:11,680 --> 00:51:13,920
and make up
for all the income I've missed.

754
00:51:14,520 --> 00:51:16,760
Fighting! Let's go!

755
00:51:25,840 --> 00:51:28,560
<i>Little Pakbung has money, money, money</i>

756
00:51:28,640 --> 00:51:31,400
<i>Money, money, money</i>

757
00:51:31,480 --> 00:51:34,000
<i>Little Pakbung has money, money, money</i>

758
00:51:34,080 --> 00:51:36,560
<i>Money, money, money</i>

759
00:51:36,640 --> 00:51:38,880
<i>Little Pakbung has money, money, money</i>

760
00:51:39,760 --> 00:51:42,640
<i>Money, money, money…</i>

761
00:51:45,840 --> 00:51:47,080
Why isn't the water running?

762
00:51:54,520 --> 00:51:55,880
The water's not working!

763
00:51:56,960 --> 00:51:58,160
Kanah!

764
00:52:03,480 --> 00:52:04,440
Hey.

765
00:52:06,640 --> 00:52:07,960
Kanah.

766
00:52:09,200 --> 00:52:11,000
The water's not running?

767
00:52:12,680 --> 00:52:15,960
Well, I was washing dishes,
and all of a sudden, it just stopped.

768
00:52:17,320 --> 00:52:20,040
Maybe the building maintenance
is fixing something?

769
00:52:21,440 --> 00:52:23,120
But the room next door
has water like normal.

770
00:52:23,200 --> 00:52:26,600
Oh? Then it's only our place
that has no water?

771
00:52:27,280 --> 00:52:29,480
- How does that even happen?
- Damn it.

772
00:52:29,560 --> 00:52:31,000
I forgot to pay the water bill.

773
00:52:31,880 --> 00:52:35,160
Hey, but usually, they have
to send us a warning notice first.

774
00:52:35,240 --> 00:52:36,960
Why did they cut it off
without warning this time?

775
00:52:37,040 --> 00:52:38,240
Actually,

776
00:52:38,320 --> 00:52:40,120
they did send one.

777
00:52:40,200 --> 00:52:41,280
But I forgot to tell you.

778
00:52:41,360 --> 00:52:44,080
Ugh, how could you forget that?

779
00:52:44,160 --> 00:52:46,440
It's so important. How could you forget?

780
00:52:47,080 --> 00:52:50,440
Bung, calm down.

781
00:52:50,520 --> 00:52:51,920
Why are you blaming Dad like that?

782
00:52:52,520 --> 00:52:53,840
He didn't mean to.

783
00:52:53,920 --> 00:52:55,360
I didn't check either.

784
00:52:55,960 --> 00:52:57,240
I'm sorry, Pakbung.

785
00:52:57,320 --> 00:52:59,360
Well, it's my fault.

786
00:52:59,960 --> 00:53:02,040
I came to stay with you.
I should've made your life easier,

787
00:53:02,120 --> 00:53:04,400
but instead, I made it more difficult.

788
00:53:04,480 --> 00:53:06,760
I'm not blaming you.

789
00:53:06,840 --> 00:53:08,000
I'm blaming myself.

790
00:53:09,880 --> 00:53:11,440
Can you not be dramatic?

791
00:53:11,520 --> 00:53:13,520
I'm mad at myself, okay?

792
00:53:17,360 --> 00:53:18,960
Are you gonna go out with foam on…

793
00:53:25,760 --> 00:53:28,400
Why am I so pissed
over something this small?

794
00:53:30,480 --> 00:53:32,360
Get it together.

795
00:53:35,800 --> 00:53:37,000
I'll call the juristic office.

796
00:53:45,200 --> 00:53:46,640
New style, Pakbung?

797
00:53:50,400 --> 00:53:51,760
Our water got cut off.

798
00:53:58,440 --> 00:53:59,720
Do you want me to help?

799
00:54:37,920 --> 00:54:40,800
There's no evidence at all
tying the attack on Ms. Darin to Rut.

800
00:54:40,880 --> 00:54:43,960
Asking the court to revoke
his temporary release would be difficult.

801
00:54:44,600 --> 00:54:48,000
Or we lure Rut
into committing another offense

802
00:54:49,760 --> 00:54:50,840
since

803
00:54:51,400 --> 00:54:52,920
he's already targeting Ms. Darin.

804
00:54:55,360 --> 00:54:57,440
- Lee!
- Ouch.

805
00:54:57,520 --> 00:54:59,400
Did you even think before you spoke?

806
00:54:59,480 --> 00:55:01,680
You want Da to be used as bait for Rut?
That's a human life.

807
00:55:02,760 --> 00:55:05,720
I'm sorry, sir. I didn't think it through.

808
00:55:06,640 --> 00:55:08,080
If Rut hurts me again,

809
00:55:09,280 --> 00:55:10,440
all this will end, right?

810
00:55:14,160 --> 00:55:15,560
That might be good.

811
00:55:17,280 --> 00:55:18,960
One life, my life,

812
00:55:20,360 --> 00:55:22,000
in exchange for everyone's peace of mind.

813
00:55:24,440 --> 00:55:26,280
That might be the best way to make amends.

814
00:55:28,480 --> 00:55:31,680
Best for who, Da?
Did you ask your mom what she thinks?

815
00:55:34,560 --> 00:55:36,280
I just wanted to help.

816
00:55:56,280 --> 00:55:57,840
<i>I helped you already, Trai.</i>

817
00:56:05,680 --> 00:56:07,600
<i>You take care of Darin.</i>

818
00:56:07,680 --> 00:56:09,000
<i>I'll take care of Pakbung for you.</i>

819
00:56:15,000 --> 00:56:16,000
Mr. Trai.

820
00:56:22,560 --> 00:56:24,240
I set a goal

821
00:56:24,320 --> 00:56:26,320
to make like one or two thousand.

822
00:56:26,400 --> 00:56:28,680
It's already midday,
and I haven't earned a single baht.

823
00:56:29,320 --> 00:56:31,840
Then here, so many clothes.
Sell them secondhand.

824
00:56:34,920 --> 00:56:37,360
Seriously? I'll really do it.

825
00:56:37,440 --> 00:56:41,400
Well, of course.
I bought them for you, so they're yours.

826
00:56:42,000 --> 00:56:45,920
You can resell them, rent them out,
wear them, whatever you want.

827
00:56:46,680 --> 00:56:49,280
You didn't just spoil me
to relieve stress, did you?

828
00:56:51,360 --> 00:56:52,440
Why?

829
00:56:53,360 --> 00:56:55,280
Did you fight with Mr. Trai?

830
00:56:56,280 --> 00:56:57,960
I have money to spare.
I feel like spending it.

831
00:56:58,560 --> 00:57:00,200
Mr. Rich Guy.

832
00:57:01,040 --> 00:57:04,560
Be honest, do you want to be
my sugar daddy or something?

833
00:57:05,680 --> 00:57:07,720
Sugar daddy? That's too old.

834
00:57:08,320 --> 00:57:11,320
Well, just brother is enough.

835
00:57:12,560 --> 00:57:13,920
Brother?

836
00:57:14,640 --> 00:57:15,600
Why?

837
00:57:17,160 --> 00:57:20,160
A big brother
can't buy things for his little sister?

838
00:57:28,200 --> 00:57:29,680
Perfect timing.

839
00:57:31,280 --> 00:57:32,480
Pakbung is my girlfriend.

840
00:57:33,560 --> 00:57:34,960
Why are you messing with her?

841
00:57:35,040 --> 00:57:36,960
Didn't I already tell you?

842
00:57:37,040 --> 00:57:38,640
If you can't take care of Pakbung,

843
00:57:39,160 --> 00:57:41,240
- then I will.
- I can take care of her myself.

844
00:57:41,320 --> 00:57:43,360
Then where have you been
since this morning?

845
00:57:43,960 --> 00:57:45,600
Where where you? Doing what? With whom?

846
00:57:47,000 --> 00:57:50,120
Hey, Trai.
The water got cut off at her place.

847
00:57:50,200 --> 00:57:51,680
Did you even know?

848
00:57:52,800 --> 00:57:53,880
The water got cut off at your place?

849
00:57:54,480 --> 00:57:57,440
When Pakbung was struggling,
when she needed you,

850
00:57:58,360 --> 00:57:59,440
what were you doing?

851
00:58:04,800 --> 00:58:07,200
Trai, pull yourself together.

852
00:58:08,360 --> 00:58:09,760
The one you should be paying attention to

853
00:58:10,360 --> 00:58:12,800
is Pakbung, not anyone else.

854
00:58:21,640 --> 00:58:23,400
I was the one who let him in,

855
00:58:23,480 --> 00:58:25,560
so I have to accept the heartbreak too.

856
00:58:25,640 --> 00:58:28,000
It's not wrong to trust someone,

857
00:58:29,520 --> 00:58:30,720
especially someone you love.

858
00:58:30,800 --> 00:58:32,560
<i>Let's try taking a break</i>
<i>from this relationship</i>

859
00:58:33,600 --> 00:58:36,040
<i>and go deal with our own problems.</i>

860
00:58:36,120 --> 00:58:37,560
So we're only going to love each other

861
00:58:38,200 --> 00:58:39,720
when we're happy?

862
00:58:41,120 --> 00:58:42,760
I will take responsibility

863
00:58:42,840 --> 00:58:44,920
by resigning as a board member,

864
00:58:45,000 --> 00:58:46,360
effective today.

865
00:58:46,440 --> 00:58:48,080
<i>I didn't sell my shares.</i>

866
00:58:48,160 --> 00:58:49,080
I gave them to him.

867
00:58:49,160 --> 00:58:51,040
What if Mr. Rachen won't give them back?

868
00:58:51,120 --> 00:58:52,720
A dirty-handed person like that

869
00:58:52,800 --> 00:58:54,360
will definitely leave some traces.

870
00:58:54,440 --> 00:58:56,680
Can you find evidence that Mrs. Mookmanee

871
00:58:57,280 --> 00:58:58,880
has done something illegal?

872
00:59:01,120 --> 00:59:02,840
Why don't you let him prove himself

873
00:59:02,920 --> 00:59:05,160
and see if he only wants money or not?

874
00:59:05,240 --> 00:59:07,520
Call your daughter,
and I'll transfer the money.

875
00:59:08,560 --> 00:59:09,760
Dad?

876
00:59:58,280 --> 01:00:01,040
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
